# Wind Speed Prediction using Machine Learning

This project applies machine learning to predict wind speed using real-world meteorological data from multiple monitoring stations in Rio de Janeiro.

## Overview

Accurate wind prediction is important for environmental monitoring and atmospheric modeling.  
This project combines data from different locations to improve predictive performance.

The model integrates:
- Local weather variables
- Data from neighboring stations
- Engineered features based on physical relationships (temperature and pressure gradients)

## Approach

- Data cleaning and preprocessing
- Feature engineering based on environmental gradients
- Training a Random Forest regression model
- Model evaluation using R² score

## Technologies

- Python
- Pandas
- NumPy
- Scikit-learn

## Key Skills Demonstrated

- Machine learning modeling
- Data processing and cleaning
- Feature engineering
- Problem-solving with real-world data

## Project Goal

The goal of this project is to demonstrate how combining domain knowledge (physics) with machine learning can improve predictions in environmental systems.
